DATE: 02 JUL XX

FROM: CDR HQDLA

TO:   CDR DDAV

SUBJ: OMA FUND INCREASE

1. REF 28 JUN XX FAX, SAB.

2. Due to the allocation of Operation and Maintenance Appropriation (OMA) funds to the operating forces, the Defense Supply Centers are experiencing a shortage of second destination transportation funds.

3. Effective immediately, the shipping service's retail stock fund will pay all transportation costs incident to the return of stock-funded material (creditable or noncreditable) to the Wholesale Supply System. However, beginning the first of next fiscal year, and each year thereafter, these costs will be included in the stock fund standard price.

4. It is anticipated, in the short run, that returns to distribution centers will decrease, then increase after the organizations stabilize their funding requirements.
